Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the rigatoni. 

Meanwhile, halve any large @Broccoli Florets{200%grams}.

When boiling, add the @Rigatoni Pasta{180%grams} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook for ~{7%minutes}.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{60%grams}. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @Breadcrumbs{25%grams} and @Olive Oil{2%tbsp} for the crumb (see pantry for amount). Season with @salt and @pepper, then set aside.

Heat your #grill{} to high. Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{260%grams} to the pan. Cook until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}, then add the garlic and fry for ~{30%seconds}. Stir in the @Creme Fraiche{150%grams}, @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%grams} and @Water{100%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for amount).

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the pasta has been cooking for 7 mins, add the broccoli florets to the pan and bring back to the boil.

Cook with the pasta until tender, ~{5%minutes} more. Once cooked, drain well in a #colander{}.

In the meantime, once the sauce has thickened, stir in the Cheddar, @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40%grams} and @Dijon Mustard{10%grams} until melted, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with @salt and @pepper, then remove from the heat.

Stir the cooked pasta and broccoli into the sauce, then transfer it into an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}.

Sprinkle over the crumbs, then pop under the grill until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch the crumbs carefully as they can burn easily.

When the chicken and broccoli pasta bake is ready, share it between your plates.

Serve the @Baby Leaf Mix{20%grams} alongside and drizzle the @Balsamic Glaze{12%ml} over them to finish. Enjoy!